extinct in England; in the US it is concentrated in FL and GA."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Alice Harnage was born about 1503, in England, United Kingdom, her father, Richard Harnage Esq, was 50 and her mother, Mrs. Richard Harnage, was 45. She married Thomas Kynaston about 1518, in Shotton, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 3 daughters."},"et":{"Abt 1503–":"umbes 1503–Surnud","1503–Female":"1503–Surnud","1499–1549":"1499–1549","1519–Female":"1519–Surnud","1520–1570":"1520–1570","1521–Male":"1521–Surnud","1526–Male":"1526–Surnud","1530–1582":"1530–1582","1455–Male":"1455–Surnud","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","ABT 1518":"umbes 1518","ABT 1519":"umbes 1519","ABT 1521":"umbes 1521","1582":"1582","1460":"1460","1570":"1570","ABT 1526":"umbes 1526","Abt 1503":"umbes 1503","1503":"1503","1455":"1455","1521":"1521","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","ABT 1530":"umbes 1530","1530":"1530","about 1486":"umbes 1486","1519":"1519","1549":"1549","1526":"1526","Shotton, Shropshire, England":"Shotton, Shropshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of,Shotton,Shropshire,England":"Shotton